<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[136,1452,337,1229]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1057,1083]" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Raddi" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[524,675,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estrellensis">
<emphasis box="[524,675,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">T. estrellensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. This species is distinguished mainly by branches slightly to sharply winged, leaves with a bullate adaxial surface and the manybranched trichomes at the base, and foveolate abaxial surface. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Raddi" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[855,1115,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estrellensis">
<emphasis box="[855,1115,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Tibouchina estrellensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Desrousseaux" baseAuthorityYear="1797" box="[1308,1452,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis box="[1308,1452,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">T. granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which differs by the flat leaves on both surfaces and the presence of basal 1–2-branched strigose trichomes on the adaxial surface. Additional illustrations in 
